{"word":"H3851 - לַהַב - lahab - lah'-hab - Blade","slug":"H3851","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לַהַב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lahab"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>lah'-hab"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Blade"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D4;&#x05D1; - lahab</b> - <i>lah'-hab</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>gleam</i>, a <i>flash</i>; figuratively a sharply polished <i>blade</i> or <i>point</i> of a weapon: - blade, bright, flame, glittering."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3827\">H3827</a>, <a href=\"#/H3852\">H3852</a>, <a href=\"#/H3853\">H3853</a>, <a href=\"#/H7957\">H7957</a>"}]}